      {
        "id" : 3,
        "title": "Sea level rise",
        "storyinfo": "The problem that arises when glaciers and sea ice melts is that the sea level rises. 8 of the 10 biggest cities in the world are close to the coast. Therefore, a lot of people's lives are affected by a sea-level rise since it plays a part in hazards from storms, flooding, and shoreline erosion. The sea level is expected to rise 25 to 30 centimeters between 2020 and 2050 in the US. In other parts of the world, the sea level is presumed to rise even more, which could be 40 to 45 centimeters. \n \n 90 percent of the world's ice is located in Antarctica, and if all the ice on Antarctica melted the sea level would rise by about 61 meters. The sea level does not have to rise much at all though to make a big impact on the world and the people. \n \n Below you can choose to see a visualization of what areas in the world that would be under sea level if it rises by 2, 4 and 6 meters.",
